%N A387575 The maximal norm of an additively indecomposable element in Shanks' simplest cubic field Q[x]/(x^3 - n*x^2 - (n+3)*x - 1).
%C A387575 For any totally real field K, an additively indecomposable element of K is a totally positive element in the maximal order of K which cannot be written as the sum of two totally positive integral elements of K. Here, an element x of K is totally positive if all conjugates of x are positive real numbers.
%C A387575 Let K be a simplest cubic field with defining polynomial f(x) = x^3 - n*x^2 - (n+3)*x - 1, and let rho be a root of f(x). Kala and Tinková classified all additively indecomposable elements of K in the case where the ring of integers O_K is Z[rho], and Gil-Muñoz and Tinková classified all additively indecomposable elements of K in the case where Z[rho] has index 3 in O_K.
