%F A387575 If n > 3 and the maximal order of Q[x]/(x^3 - n*x^2 - (n+3)*x - 1) is generated by a root of x^3 - n*x^2 - (n+3)*x - 1, then a(n) = ((n^2 + 3*n + 9)^2)/27 if n == 0 (mod 3), else a(n) = (n^4 + 6*n^3 + 24*n^2 + 47*n + 57)/27 if n == 1 (mod 3), else a(n) == (n^4 + 6*n^3 + 24*n^2 + 43*n + 51)/27 if n = 2 (mod 3) [Tinková, Theorem 1.2].
%F A387575 If the order Z[rho] generated by a root rho of x^3 - n*x^2 - (n+3)*x - 1 has index 3 in the maximal order of Q[x]/(x^3 - n*x^2 - (n+3)*x - 1), then a(n) = (2*n^3 + 9*n^2 + 27*n + 27)/27 if n <= 48, otherwise a(n) = ((n^2 + 3*n + 9)^2)/729 [Gil-Muñoz--Tinková, Proposition 6.4]. - _Robin Visser_, Nov 07 2025
%e A387575 For n = 0, every additively indecomposable element in Q[x]/(x^3 - 3*x - 1) has norm either 1, 3, or 9, thus a(0) = 9.
%e A387575 For n = 1, every additively indecomposable element in Q[x]/(x^3 - x^2 - 4*x - 1) has norm either 1, 5, or 13, thus a(1) = 13.
%e A387575 For n = 2, every additively indecomposable element in Q[x]/(x^3 - 2*x^2 - 5*x - 1) has norm either 1, 7, 11, or 19, thus a(2) = 19.
